problem_text: m \angle BZD = 107, m \angle FZE = 2x+5, m \angle CZD = x, what is the measure of \angle FZE?
proof:
Step 1:
Theorem: Known facts
Premises : start
Conclusions: Z on CF, pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠FZE, Z on BH, Z on DI, D on JZ, ∠KZJ, ∠KZL, Z on FK, 3.14 = pi, pi * (107 / 180) = ∠DZB, ∠DZK, ∠FZE, ∠IZH, ∠CZL, Z on IJ, pi * (x / 180) = ∠DZC, ∠DZK, ∠FZI, C on KZ, B on LZ, E on HZ, ∠FZH, ∠IZE, ∠EZI, ∠IZF

Step 2:
Theorem: Vertical Angle Theorem
Premises : Z on BH, Z on CF
Conclusions: ∠CZB = ∠FZH

Step 3:
Theorem: Vertical Angle Theorem
Premises : Z on BH, Z on DI
Conclusions: ∠DZB = ∠IZH

Step 4:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : D on JZ, ∠KZJ
Conclusions: ∠KZD = ∠KZJ

Step 5:
Theorem: Evaluate
Premises : 3.14 = pi
Conclusions: 1.87 = pi * (107 / 180)

Step 6:
Theorem: Reverse Angle Definition
Premises : ∠DZK
Conclusions: ∠DZK = 2 * pi - ∠KZD

Step 7:
Theorem: Vertical Angle Theorem
Premises : Z on IJ, Z on FK
Conclusions: ∠FZI = ∠KZJ

Step 8:
Theorem: Reverse Angle Definition
Premises : ∠FZI
Conclusions: ∠FZI = 2 * pi - ∠IZF

Step 9:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠DZK, C on KZ
Conclusions: ∠DZC = ∠DZK

Step 10:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : C on KZ, ∠KZL
Conclusions: ∠CZL = ∠KZL

Step 11:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠CZL, B on LZ
Conclusions: ∠CZB = ∠CZL

Step 12:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : B on LZ, ∠KZL
Conclusions: ∠KZB = ∠KZL

Step 13:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠IZH, E on HZ
Conclusions: ∠IZE = ∠IZH

Step 14:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠FZH, E on HZ
Conclusions: ∠FZE = ∠FZH

Step 15:
Theorem: Reverse Angle Definition
Premises : ∠IZE
Conclusions: ∠IZE = 2 * pi - ∠EZI

Step 16:
Theorem: Circumference splited
Premises : ∠FZE, ∠IZF, ∠EZI
Conclusions: 2 * pi = ∠EZI + ∠FZE + ∠IZF

Step 17:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠DZB = ∠IZH, pi * (107 / 180) = ∠DZB
Conclusions: pi * (107 / 180) = ∠IZH

Step 18:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠FZI = 2 * pi - ∠IZF, ∠FZI = ∠KZJ
Conclusions: ∠KZJ = 2 * pi - ∠IZF

Step 19:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi * (x / 180) = ∠DZC, ∠DZC = ∠DZK
Conclusions: pi * (x / 180) = ∠DZK

Step 20:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠CZB = ∠CZL, ∠CZL = ∠KZL
Conclusions: ∠CZB = ∠KZL

Step 21:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠FZE, ∠FZE = ∠FZH
Conclusions: pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠FZH

Step 22:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi * (107 / 180) = ∠IZH, ∠IZE = ∠IZH
Conclusions: pi * (107 / 180) = ∠IZE

Step 23:
Theorem: Substitution
Premises : ∠KZJ = 2 * pi - ∠IZF, 3.14 = pi
Conclusions: ∠KZJ = 2 * 3.14 - ∠IZF

Step 24:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠DZK = 2 * pi - ∠KZD, pi * (x / 180) = ∠DZK
Conclusions: pi * (x / 180) = 2 * pi - ∠KZD

Step 25:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠CZB = ∠KZL, ∠CZB = ∠FZH, pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠FZH
Conclusions: pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠KZL

Step 26:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠IZE = 2 * pi - ∠EZI, pi * (107 / 180) = ∠IZE
Conclusions: pi * (107 / 180) = 2 * pi - ∠EZI

Step 27:
Theorem: Substitution
Premises : pi * (x / 180) = 2 * pi - ∠KZD, 3.14 = pi, ∠KZD = ∠KZJ
Conclusions: 3.14 * (x / 180) = 2 * 3.14 - ∠KZJ

Step 28:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠KZB = ∠KZL, pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠KZL
Conclusions: pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠KZB

Step 29:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi * (107 / 180) = 2 * pi - ∠EZI, 1.87 = pi * (107 / 180)
Conclusions: 1.87 = 2 * pi - ∠EZI

Step 30:
Theorem: Substitution
Premises : pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠KZB, 3.14 = pi
Conclusions: 3.14 * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠KZB

Step 31:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠KZB, 3.14 * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠KZB
Conclusions: 3.14 * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180)

Step 32:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : 3.14 * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180), pi * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠FZE
Conclusions: 3.14 * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠FZE

Step 33:
Theorem: Solve Linear Equation System
Premises : ∠KZJ = 2 * 3.14 - ∠IZF, 3.14 * ((5 + 2 * x) / 180) = ∠FZE, 3.14 * (x / 180) = 2 * 3.14 - ∠KZJ, 2 * pi = ∠EZI + ∠FZE + ∠IZF, 1.87 = 2 * pi - ∠EZI
Conclusions: 1.27 = ∠FZE
logic_fomrs_refined: Equals(MeasureOf(Angle(F, Z, E)), Mul(pi, Div(Add(Mul(2.0, x), 5.0), 180.0)))
